Message.Title: Caution will be good
Message.Msg: It is showing a little dizziness at the top. A correction is overdue but it should not be like the one which Apple underwent! That is highly unlikely, but what could be the supports now? Will it rebound from $880 which seems to be a recent breakout point? Or will that crack to take it lower? Beyond $840, all levels were new and supports / resistances have not been decisively proven. They have been tested once, but that is never enough to be convincing. The crucial averages are deep down so there may be support before that. On the upside, $920 will be a strong resistance as people may start to get a little edgy. If it fails there twice, then a range bound trade scenario may emerge. Meanwhile, fighting patent infringement lawsuits and privacy allegations, Google is moving towards a full launch of the Glass. All these patent and other cases have dented the reputation of Google. These lawsuits are increasing all the time, like the multi-billion dollar patent infringement lawsuit by MGT Capital Investment (MGT) against casino gaming companies. Filing such lawsuits is now a business model to leverage the value of the patents. More importantly for Google, the privacy issues are being stoked by Microsoft with a lot of enthusiasm. Still the admirers or addicts or dependents, whatever you call the users, can not live without Google. And that is the biggest advantage which Google possesses. But whether the price already factors this near-indispensability is a good question. The next few weeks will determine whether the stock is able to show strength again or it starts to show fatigue. Caution is strongly advised. It is quite possible that it becomes a trading stock with a defined range before it decides where it wants to go, ultimately.
